---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="What is themx and how to use the generated prompts">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold" style="font-family: var(--tx-font-heading); color: var(--tx-text);">About themx</h1>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--tx-text-muted);">
      <p>
        <strong style="color: var(--tx-text);">themx</strong> is a curated catalog of web design trends and styles.
        Each theme includes visual previews, color palettes, typography recommendations, and key
        characteristics that define the style.
      </p>

      <p>
        The real power is in the <strong style="color: var(--tx-text);">prompt builder</strong>. Configure your
        tech stack and desired components, and themx generates a ready-to-use prompt you can paste
        directly into Claude to build your next project in any design style.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold pt-4" style="font-family: var(--tx-font-heading); color: var(--tx-text);">How to Use</h2>

      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>Browse themes on the homepage or filter by category and year</li>
        <li>Click a theme to see its details — colors, typography, characteristics</li>
        <li>Use the prompt builder to select your framework, CSS approach, and components</li>
        <li>Click "Copy to Clipboard" and paste the prompt into Claude</li>
        <li>Claude will generate code matching that design style</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold pt-4" style="font-family: var(--tx-font-heading); color: var(--tx-text);">Categories</h2>

      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li><strong style="color: var(--tx-text);">Minimalist</strong> — Clean, whitespace-heavy, typography-focused</li>
        <li><strong style="color: var(--tx-text);">Bold</strong> — High contrast, thick borders, attention-grabbing</li>
        <li><strong style="color: var(--tx-text);">Elegant</strong> — Refined, luxurious, sophisticated effects</li>
        <li><strong style="color: var(--tx-text);">Playful</strong> — Fun, colorful, experimental layouts</li>
        <li><strong style="color: var(--tx-text);">Corporate</strong> — Professional, structured, widely adopted</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
